hopobject.body: Please call back later biotech pharma services Noninterest expense, excluding nonperforming asset expense and early extinguishment of debt expense, was $56.1 million for the second quarter of 2013, compared to $51.2 million for the first quarter of 2013. The increase of $4.9 million, or 9.6%, was primarily the result of a $3.3 million increase in performance-based incentives as a result of improved performance, as well as an increase in salary cost related to an increase in the total number of employees at Cole Taylor Mortgage.
